name: Inshallah Book
description: Inshallah is a compendium of the photographs and diaries that I took and wrote during the 9 days I spent in Morocco in April 2009. The book is professionally printed on heavy glossy paper and it is composed by 48 pages that host more than 130 colour photographs and texts that have never been published before. It is printed in a limited signed edition of 13 and there are only 4 left. You can view some of the images inside the book here.

name: Omens Print
description:
One 50x75cm print on Archival C Print Professional Mate Paper.

This print is from my 'I wish I knew how it would feel to be Free' solo exhibition and the colours of the photograph look gorgeous on this large print. 

The print has some creases on the right side but I think that they will be less noticeable once it's framed (see photograph of the actual print for reference). Because of this, it is marked at 50% less than it's original price.

The print is signed and dated.

name: Sister of the moon Diptych
description:
Two 40x25 cm prints on Archival C Print Professional Mate Paper which are mounted on lightweight poster board (which can be removed at the buyer's request).

This print is from my 'I wish I knew how it would feel to be Free' solo exhibition. The print has some almost invisible scuffs at the edges but they wouldn't be noticeable once the prints are framed. Because of this it is marked at 40% less than it's original price.

The print is signed and dated.

name: Mi Mala Estrella Tetraptych
description:
Four 14x20cm prints on Archival C Print Professional Mate Paper.

This Tetraptych is one of my personal favourites. They are marked down at 80% of their original price because each of the prints have creases on the left side, some are slighter than others. As you can see in the actual pictures of the prints these defects are small and probably won't be noticeable once the prints are framed.

All of the photographs are signed and dated.

name: Incantations Print
description:
One 32x48cm print on Archival C Print Professional Mate Paper.

This print is from my 'I wish I knew how it would feel to be Free' solo exhibition. The print has some large creases in the corners but I think that they will be less noticeable once it's framed (see photograph of the actual print for reference). Because of this, it is marked at 60% less than it's original price.

The print is signed and dated.
